==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sultana
<hw>Sul*ta"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The wife of a sultan; a sultaness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>A kind of seedless raisin produced
near <city>Smyrna</city> in Asiatic Turkey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sultana bird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
hyacinthine, or purple, gallinule. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Gallinule</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sultanate</ent>⟦br⟧
